TEXT.0: 1: The Interstellar Boundary Explorer (IBEX) has operated in space since 2008 updating our knowledge of the outer heliosphere and its interaction with the local interstellar medium. Start-time: 2008-12-25. There are currently 15 releases of IBEX-HI and/or IBEX-LO data covering 2009-2017.

TEXT.1: 2: This data set is from the Release 7 (6 months-cadence) IBEX-Lo map data for the first seven years, 2009-2015, in the form of omnidirectional fluxes with no corrections (nocg) for spacecraft motion (Compton-Getting) and no ENA survival probability (nosp) between 1 and 100 AU.

TEXT.2: 3: The data consist of all-sky maps in Solar Ecliptic Longitude (east and west) and Latitude angles for ENA (hydrogen) fluxes from IBEX-Lo energy bands 1-8 in numerical data form. Energy channels 1-8 have FWHM center-point energies at 0.015, 0.029, 0.055, 0.110, 0.209, 0.439, 0.872, 1.821 keV, respectively. Details of the data and enabled science from Release 10 are given in the following journal publication:

TEXT.3: 4: S.A. Fuselier et al., The IBEX-Lo Sensor. Space Sci Rev (2009) 146: 117...147; DOI 10.1007/s11214-009-9495-8

TEXT.5: 6. The following codes are used to define dataset types:

TEXT.6: cg = Compton-Getting corrections have been applied to the data to account for the speed of the spacecraft relative to the direction of arrival of the ENAs.

TEXT.8: sp = survival probability corrections have been applied to the data to account for the loss of ENAs due to radiation pressure, photoionization and ionization via charge exchange with solar wind protons as they stream through the heliosphere. This correction scales the data out from IBEX at 1 AU to ~100 AU. In the original data this mode is denoted as Tabular.

TEXT.9: noSP - no survival probability corrections have been applied to the data.

TEXT.11: ram = data was collected when the spacecraft was ramming into the incoming ENAs.

TEXT.12: antiram = data was collected when the spacecraft was moving away from the incoming ENAs.

TEXT.13: 7. The following list associates Release 10 map numbers (1-14) with mission year (1-7), orbits (11-310b), and dates (12/25/2008-12/23/2015):

TEXT.28: 8: The energy resolution is delta-E/E = 0.8 for all channels:

TEXT.37: 9: This particular data set, denoted in the original ascii files as lvset_h_mapN for N=1,10, includes pixel map data from all directions (omnidirectional), no CG, no SP, 6 month cadence.

Logical_source_description.0: IBEX-Lo Release-07; no Compton-Getting, no Survival-Probability, Omnidirectional 6-month-Average West Ecliptic Maps

Rules_of_use.0: The IBEX Release 7 data are archived as fully citable data. Please consult IBEX team publications and personnel for further details on production, processing, and usage of these data.

Acknowledgement.0: Please acknowledge the IBEX Mission Principal Investigator, Dr. David J McComas of Princeton University.
